# OmniRoute PR-Pipeline Roadmap — 2026 Q3

This is the audit-derived PR plan. Each row is a candidate PR. PRs are grouped into
12 categories and 4 ship-priority tiers. **Not all of these will land** — the
maintainer has limited review bandwidth and an in-flight Bifrost migration, so
prioritization is essential.

Audit data is in `__open.json`, `__open_clean.json`, `__all_prs.json` (root) for
re-running on a fresh `upstream/main`.

---

## Tier 1 — Mechanical, fully additive, lowest risk (sprint 1)

These are 1-3 hour PRs that touch one file and one concern. Safe to land in any
order. Each can be cut from `upstream/main` without conflicting with Bifrost work.

| ID | Category | Title | Effort | Files |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| PR-A-001 | A | `chore(types): remove @ts-nocheck in open-sse/utils/usageTracking.ts` (529 lines — biggest one) | 2h | 1 |
| PR-A-002 | A | `chore(types): remove @ts-nocheck in src/lib/db/index.ts` | 2h | 1 |
| PR-A-003 | A | `chore(types): remove @ts-nocheck in open-sse/executors/base.ts:1` | 1h | 1 |
| PR-A-004 | A | `chore(types): remove @ts-nocheck in open-sse/lib/cacheKey.ts` | 1h | 1 |
| PR-A-005..030 | A | one PR per remaining `@ts-ignore`/`@ts-expect-error` directive | 1h each | 1 |
| PR-B-001..025 | B | `eslint-disable` removal in 25 files (one per file) | 1h each | 1 |
| PR-B-100 | B | `chore(eslint): enable no-explicit-any as error in .eslintrc` (gates future drift) | 30m | 1 |
| PR-D-001..025 | D | Empty catch hardening in 25 files (one per file) | 30m each | 1 |
| PR-D-100 | D | `chore(eslint): enable no-empty as error in .eslintrc` | 30m | 1 |
| PR-G-001..015 | G | Dead code elimination (knip-driven) in 15 modules | 1h each | 1-3 |
| PR-G-100 | G | `ci: add knip --reporter json step to quality.yml` | 30m | 1 |

**Subtotal: ~100 PRs at avg 1h each = ~12.5 working days.**

---

## Tier 2 — Issue-shaped, requires investigation (sprint 2)

Each is a user-filed issue or a TODO/FIXME that needs verification on current
`main` before fix. Issues #6146, #6147, #6148, #6150 are larger features that
should be sliced into multiple PRs each.

| ID | Category | Title | Effort | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| PR-C-001..010 | C | TODO/FIXME/XXX/HACK resolution (10 PRs, one per cluster) | 2h each | verify each on main |
| PR-H-001..050 | H | User-filed open issues (59 total — pick high-leverage first) | varies | see issues #6144 (done), #6146, #6147, #6148, #6149, #6150 |
| PR-J-001..010 | J | console.log → structured logger migration | 2h each | 1,239 calls across codebase |
| PR-K-001..010 | K | Doc-staleness PRs (AGENTS.md count blocks) | 30m each | already gated by check:doc-counts |

**Subtotal: ~80 PRs at avg 2h each = ~20 working days.**

---

## Tier 3 — Type-system strengthening (sprint 3)

Each requires defining new interfaces in `src/shared/types/` then migrating one
file per PR. Heavier per-PR effort, more architectural risk.

| ID | Category | Title | Effort |
|---|---|---|---|
| PR-E-001 | E | Define `OmniRouteExecutor` interface in `src/shared/types/` | 4h |
| PR-E-002..030 | E | Migrate 30 executor files to use the new interface (one per file) | 2h each |
| PR-E-100 | E | `chore(eslint): enable no-explicit-any as error` | 30m |
| PR-I-001..020 | I | Test coverage gap PRs (20 modules) | 1.5h each |

**Subtotal: ~55 PRs at avg 2h each = ~14 working days.**

---

## Tier 4 — Structural decomposition (sprint 4+)

God-file decomposition and Bifrost-aligned architecture work. Each is multi-week.

| ID | Category | Title | Effort |
|---|---|---|---|
| PR-F-001 | F | Decompose `combos/page.tsx` (4,363 lines) into 12 component files | 1 week |
| PR-F-002..020 | F | Decompose remaining 20 files > 1000 lines | 3 days each |
| PR-L-001..015 | L | Observability hooks (Otel spans, structured error events) | 3 days each |

**Subtotal: ~35 PRs at avg 4 days each = ~140 working days.**

---

## Total

- **Tier 1 (mechanical):** ~100 PRs / ~12 days
- **Tier 2 (issue-shaped):** ~80 PRs / ~20 days
- **Tier 3 (type system):** ~55 PRs / ~14 days
- **Tier 4 (structural):** ~35 PRs / ~140 days
- **TOTAL:** ~270 PRs / ~186 days (one developer)

**Realistic ship count** at maintainer's review throughput (~5 PRs/week): 100-150 PRs over 6 months.

