## Already shipped this session (committed benchmarks)

- **PR #6151** — Tier 1, Category custom (agent-index generator + drift gate). 7 files / +961/-4 across 2 commits.
- **PR #6166** — Tier 1, Category H (issue #6144 fix). 3 files / +84/-8, 1 commit.

These two establish the contribution pattern: small, focused, fully additive, tested.

---

## Convention for new PRs

```
feat|fix|chore(scope): summary (issue #NNNN)

Body explains:
- What the issue is
- Why this PR fixes it
- How to verify (test command)
- What follow-ups remain
```

Branches cut from `upstream/main`, force-pushed to `KooshaPari/OmniRoute`,
PRs opened against `diegosouzapw/OmniRoute:main` via `gh pr create`.

---

## Re-running the audit

```bash
gh issue list --repo diegosouzapw/OmniRoute --state open --limit 200 \
  --json number,title,labels,createdAt > __open.json
gh pr list --repo diegosouzapw/OmniRoute --state all --limit 150 \
  --json number,title,state,createdAt,mergedAt > __all_prs.json

# Strip ANSI codes from output (gh emits them in JSON output):
powershell -NoProfile -Command "(Get-Content '__open.json' -Raw) -replace \`"\x1B\[[0-9;]*[mGKHJ]\`", '' | Out-File '__open_clean.json' -Encoding utf8"
```

Re-run quarterly to capture new issues.